Growing trade & more open markets have lifted hundreds of millions out of extreme poverty in recent decades. 

Though much remains to be done to further reduce poverty & improve @wto, we require an effective rules based trading system to recover & create even more opportunity.

Australia looks forward to working with other nations to appoint a new @wto Director-General for the post #COVID19 era.

They will need to advance new rules from protecting our fisheries to embracing e-commerce, drive transparency & help to restore effective dispute resolution.

Thank you @WTODGAZEVEDO for your service & commitment to global trade policy in leading @wto since 2013.

Though you have served in challenging times you have been a well considered advocate for the global rules based trading system.

Best wishes for the next steps in your life.
